OL,3,CPrincess of Wales lays wreath at
OL,4,CCenotaph to mark Anzac day
OL,6,FReciting The Fallen, by English poet
OL,7,FLaurence Binyon, Reverend Dr Lyndon
OL,8,FDrake said: "They shall grow not old,
OL,9,Fas we that are left grow old; age
OL,10,Fshall not weary them nor the years
OL,11,Fcondemn. At the going down of the sun
OL,12,Fand in the morning, we will remember
OL,13,Fthem."
OL,15,FA Royal Marines Portsmouth Road Band
OL,16,Ftrumpeter played the last post and a
OL,17,Fone-minute silence followed.
OL,26,@pD@MOUuD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
