OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1777277174
OL,3,CPrincess of Wales lays wreath at
OL,4,CCenotaph to mark Anzac day
OL,6,FKate joined attendees singing the
OL,7,Fhymn, O God Our Help in Ages Past,
OL,8,Fbefore the men and women in military
OL,9,Funiforms marched off Whitehall.
OL,11,FThe princess, wearing a New Zealand
OL,12,FAnzac remembrance poppy, then joined a
OL,13,Fcommemoration and thanksgiving service
OL,14,Fat Westminster Abbey on Saturday
OL,15,Fafternoon, including prayers from
OL,16,Fchildren of each country and a
OL,17,Ftraditional waiata sung by London-
OL,18,Fbased Maori culture group Ngati Ranana.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
