OL,3,CPrincess of Wales lays wreath at
OL,4,CCenotaph to mark Anzac day
OL,6,FIn an address, the Very Reverend
OL,7,FJoanne Kelly-Moore said: "As dawn
OL,8,Fbreaks across our world on this Anzac
OL,9,FDay, it does so again in places marked
OL,10,Fby conflict and fear, in Iran and
OL,11,Fthroughout the Middle East, Ukraine,
OL,12,FSudan, Myanmar, and in other regions
OL,13,Ftorn apart by the reality of war and
OL,14,Fviolence.
OL,16,F"Lives disrupted, communities torn
OL,17,Fapart, innocent suffering the
OL,18,Fconsequences of human hatred and
OL,19,Fdivision today.
OL,26,@oD@ZOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
