OL,3,CPrincess of Wales lays wreath at
OL,4,CCenotaph to mark Anzac day
OL,6,FThe day was also marked in Villers-
OL,7,FBretonneux, a village in the Somme
OL,8,Fregion of France, which Australian
OL,9,Funits helped defend during the First
OL,10,FWorld War.
OL,12,FA post on the Royal Family X account
OL,13,Fon Saturday morning said: "Today is
OL,14,F_ANZACDay ` which honours the members
OL,15,Fof the Australian and New Zealand Army
OL,16,FCorps (ANZAC) who served and died in
OL,17,Fall wars, conflicts and peacekeeping
OL,18,Foperations."
